description: {"blocks":[{"key":"1heqj","text":"This protocol was used to generate a single cell suspension from transbronchial biopsies from human lung. The procedure is carried out on ice, reducing artifact gene expression changes. Cell yield / mg is \u003e5000 cells/mg with 80-90% viability (trypan blue dye exclusion). 10X scRNA-seq data is high quality (3'v3.1 and 5' v1.1) with \u003e74% of cells retained after initial QC filtering (\u003c20% mitochondrial gene reads, \u003e500 genes/cell and \u003e800 RNA molecules/cell). Expression of IER genes FOS and JUN is low in integrated, QC filtered dataset (normalized avg gene expression \u003c3). Cell populations identified in single cell data  630 µL DPBS (no Ca, no Mg - MLS)
 +13 mg tissue per 1 mL enzyme mix
